          caches:
              class-by-id:	
                  valueClass: com.bac.DOClass
                  cache-provider: eh_cache

The Caching Configuration (Ehcache):
You are using Ehcache (a popular Java-based caching library) to store com.bac.DOClass objects in memory.
How it works:
When your application needs a DOClass object (likely a Data Object used during conversion), it follows this flow:
Check Cache: It looks in the class-by-id cache.
Cache Hit: If found, it returns the object immediately (Microseconds).
Cache Miss: If not found, it queries the Database (Mongo/SQL), populates the cache, and then returns the object (Milliseconds).

Why use "class-by-id" for Data Conversion?
In a Mongo-to-SQL migration, you often have Reference Data (like Product Categories or Tax Codes).
Instead of querying the database for the same Category 10,000 times during a bulk migration, Ehcache stores it in the JVM's memory.

@Service
public class ConversionService {
    @Cacheable(value = "class-by-id", key = "#id")
    public DOClass getReferenceData(String id) {
        // This only runs if the data is NOT in Ehcache
        return mongoRepository.findById(id);
    }
}


